===Etymology===
From Old French [[sucre]] ("sugar") < Medieval Latin ''succarum'' < Arabic {{ARchar|[[سكر|سُكّر]]}} (súkkar) < Persian {{FAchar|[[شکر]]}} (shekar) < Sanskrit [[शर्करा]] (sharkara) "ground or candied sugar," originally "grit," "gravel" (cognate with Greek [[κρόκη]] "pebble").

